erms.&#10;&#10;2. Definitions&#10;HandyManService: Refers to the platform providing access to handyman services and a shopping marketplace for tools and hardware.&#10;User: Any individual or entity utilizing HandyManService.&#10;Services: Professional handyman services offered, including:&#10;&#10;Carpentry&#10;  Carpentry is the skilled trade of working with wood and other materials to construct, repair, or install structures and furnishings. Carpenters typically create or fix frameworks, furniture, doors, &#10;  windows, cabinets, and other wood-based items. They may also work on finishing elements like trim and molding to enhance a building's aesthetic.&#10;&#10;&#10;Applications:&#10;  Building custom furniture, such as shelves or tables.&#10;  Repairing broken wooden fixtures.&#10;  Installing cabinets and countertops in kitchens.&#10;  Framing walls, doors, and windows during construction.&#10;  Crafting intricate woodworks for aesthetic appeal.&#10;  Common Tools: Hammer, saws, drills, chisels, and tape measures.&#10;&#10;&#10;Plumbing&#10;  Plumbing involves the installation, maintenance, and repair of systems that convey water, gas, and waste in a building. Plumbers ensure that homes and businesses have functional water and &#10;  drainage systems.&#10;&#10;&#10;Applications:&#10;  Fixing leaking faucets and pipes.&#10;  Installing or repairing toilets, sinks, and bathtubs.&#10;  Maintaining hot water systems and heaters.&#10;  Clearing clogged drains.&#10;  Setting up gas and water connections in new constructions.&#10;  Common Tools: Pipe wrenches, plungers, augers, soldering tools, and pipe cutters.&#10;&#10;&#10;Painting&#10;  Painting services include the application of paint, varnishes, or other finishes to walls, ceilings, furniture, or exteriors. This service enhances the aesthetic and protective qualities of a structure or &#10;  object.&#10;&#10;&#10;Applications:&#10;  Interior and exterior wall painting for homes and offices.&#10;  Applying protective coatings to prevent weather damage.&#10;  Restoring furniture with fresh finishes or paint.&#10;  Creating decorative patterns or accent walls.&#10;  Spray-painting for industrial or automotive purposes.&#10;  Common Tools: Brushes, rollers, sprayers, scrapers, and sandpaper.&#10;&#10;&#10;4. Electrical Work&#10;  Electrical work focuses on the installation, repair, and maintenance of electrical systems and components. Electricians ensure safe and functional electrical circuits for homes and businesses.&#10;&#10;Applications:&#10;  Wiring new constructions or remodeling existing systems.&#10;  Installing lighting fixtures, outlets, and switches.&#10;  Repairing circuit breakers and electrical panels.&#10;  Setting up smart home systems and appliances.&#10;  Diagnosing and fixing electrical faults.&#10;  Common Tools: Multimeters, pliers, wire strippers, screwdrivers, and voltage testers.&#10;&#10;5. Cleaning&#10;  Cleaning services cater to maintaining cleanliness and hygiene in residential, commercial, and industrial spaces. It can include routine, deep, or specialized cleaning tasks.&#10;&#10;Applications:&#10;  General home cleaning, including dusting, vacuuming, and mopping.&#10;  Commercial cleaning for offices and retail spaces.&#10;  Deep cleaning for kitchens, bathrooms, or upholstery.&#10;  Post-construction cleanup to remove debris and dust.&#10;  Specialized cleaning for carpets, windows, and hard-to-reach areas.&#10;  Common Tools: Mops, vacuums, cleaning solutions, microfiber cloths, and squeegees.&#10;&#10;6. Flooring&#10;  Flooring services involve the installation, repair, and maintenance of floor surfaces to ensure durability, functionality, and aesthetic appeal. Professionals work with materials such as wood, tiles, &#10;  vinyl, and concrete.&#10;&#10;Applications:&#10;  Installing hardwood, laminate, or tile floors.&#10;  Polishing and refinishing existing floors to restore shine.&#10;  Repairing cracked or uneven flooring.&#10;  Applying 